I"°<p>Epistemic action refers to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-movement-supports-spatial-reasoning">movements</a> which are primarily conducted to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/consciousness-contains-transient-latent-representations">store and manipulate transient representations stored exosomatically</a>, such as scribbling on a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/drawing-surfaces-extend-visuospatial-sketchpad">sketchpad</a>. In this epistemic action generalizes the offsourcing of cognitive tasks to external <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/virtual-reality-renders-abstract-concepts-into-tangible-objects">physical objects</a>.</p>
